						<summary>

						<p>On a stone near the Abbā-maṭha.</p>						

						<p>The record is dated Śaka 1388, <hi rend="italic">Vyaya, Phālguṇa,</hi> ba. 30, solar eclipse, corresponding to A.D. 1467, March 6.</p>						

						<p>Damaged and worn out. Seems to record certain grants for worship and offerings of the local deity. Mēḍēkurti is referred to as a <hi rend="italic">Nāyaṅkara</hi> village in Niṭṭūri-<hi rend="italic">sthaḷa.</hi> Refers to Mahāmaṇḍalēśvara [Mūpana]-nāyaka and Mallayadeva mahārāja and at the end of the inscription Narasiṅga choḍa, whose inter-relationship is not clear.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
